definitions.definition: A device with interlocking parts used for fastening things together, such as a fastener or a holder .
examples: I always have a hard time working the clasp on this necklace!

definitions.definition: A bar or insignia on a medal ribbon, to either indicate an additional award of the medal, or the action or service for which it was awarded.
An embrace , a grasp , or handshake .
examples: He took her hand in a firm clasp .

main_definition: ( countable ) A device with interlocking parts used for fastening things together, such as a fastener or a holder .

( uncountable ) An embrace , a grasp , or handshake .
